SIMPLE: womanish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Womanish
<hw>Wom"an*ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Suitable to a
woman, having the qualities of a woman; effeminate; not becoming a man;
-- usually in a reproachful sense. See the Note under
<er>Effeminate</er>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ Thy tears are
<xex>womanish</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧ <xex>Womanish</xex>
entreaties.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A voice not soft, weak, piping, and <qex>womanish</qex>, but
audible, strong, and manlike.</q> <rj><qau>Ascham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Wom"an*ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Wom"an*ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Womanize</ent>⟦br⟧
